<docbook><section><title>GlossaryEntryBadParentLinks</title><para> </para><bridgehead class="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml:h3">BadParentLinks</bridgehead>
<para>The BadParentLinks parameter appears in the [AutoRepair] section of your virtuoso.ini file.
 Occasionally, internal errors may occur in your database.
 Moreover, these errors may result in a loss of integrity of references.
 If you enable BadParentLinks, you permit the database to automatically repair these references, without incurring a crash dump and subsequent restore.
 OpenLink suggests that you set BadParentLinks to 0.
</para></section></docbook>